cs.RO, cs.GT, cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.SG 

This paper deals with the problem of optimal path planning in different homotopy classes in a given environment, which is a common problem in robotics applications. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses the construction of presentations of fundamental groups and algorithms for solving the word problem in such groups, which falls under the sub-category of cs.GT (Computational Geometry). The paper also deals with configuration spaces, which is a topic in cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper presents results in the coordination space of robots navigating on an Euclidean plane, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SG (Simulation and Gaming).
